      • actionPerformed

        public void actionPerformed(java.awt.event.ActionEvent e)
        Getting the text from the textfield when the user push 'Enter'. If the text entered starts with an '/', it indicates that this is a command to the server. Then we parse out the actual to command to send to the server, and finally we find the message that follows the command. If it is not a command, the nick of the sender is displayed in the textarea together with the written message, and the message is also sent to the server.
        Specified by:
        actionPerformed in interface java.awt.event.ActionListener
        Parameters:
        e - The actual event.
